<kml>
<property-doc name=Relative-Combat-Power>
<system-documentation name=Relative-Combat-Power>
<gpd-documentation name=CritiqueScores>

<description>
Combat power is a subjective term used to measure the effectiveness of a force.  It considers raw strength of soldiers and their weapons, moral strength, morale, state of training, state of combat experience, supply status, etc.  Relative combat power is a comparison of similar factors between Red and Blue.
</description>

<example>
What is the overall relative combat power for this COA?<br><br>
What is the relative combat power at the point of decision for this COA?<br><br>
Is there an acceptable balance between the relative combat power in the main and supporting efforts?<br><br>
</example>

</kml>
